data.description: Beautiful Year-round Mountain Home with Million Dollar Views. Completely remodeled in 1992, the home sits on 1.76 wooded acres with exceptional views of Wild Basin, Rocky Mountain National Park and the Continental Divide. Open Floor Plan, Vaulted Ceilings, Gas Log Sandstone Fireplace, upper and lower decks to enjoy the views and wildlife. Master Suite, skylights, hot water heat, and amenities too numerous to mention. A must see...you will never want to leave!
data.whatILove: This is a home, not just a house.  It is warm, inviting, and cozy while situated on a most spectacular panoramic view lot.  Located equi-distant between Lyons and Estes Park.  It has a perfect setup for a Bed and Breakfast with great separation of space between the bedrooms.  Highly recommend you take a look at this spectacular property!
